headline: Review & Preview: An Everything Rally Rolls On
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average added 0.1% for its seventh 2025 closing record, the S&P 500 rose 0.4% for its 28th record, and the Nasdaq Composite was up 0.7% for its 29th record of the year.  The personal consumption expenditures price index, the Federal Reserve’s preferred inflation gauge, is due on Friday.  Last week’s quarter-point interest rate cut might have lowered the excitement a bit, but the PCE report still has the power to upend the bullish narrative, given that markets appear to be counting on a coming string of rate cuts.
